==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic *''wegan''.  Cognate with Old Saxon ''[[#Old Saxon|wegan]]'' (Dutch ''[[wegen]]''), Old High German ''[[#Old High German|wegan]]'' (German ''[[bewegen]]''), Old Norse ''[[vega]]'', Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐍅𐌹𐌲𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈweɣɑn/}}

===Verb===
'''wegan''' (class V strong: ''3 singular preterite'' '''[[wæg|wæġ]]''', ''preterite plural'' '''[[wægon|wǣgon]]''', ''past participle'' (ġe)'''[[wegen]]''')

# to [[carry]], [[bear]]
# to [[wear]]
# to [[carry on]], [[inflict]]
# to [[weigh]], [[consider]]

